@startuml api-comfyui-binding
!theme plain
title Binding sequence — spec load → typed node class → graph execution
skinparam defaultFontName Inconsolata
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor        User                         as U
participant "loader.py"                   as LD
participant "spec_kinds.py"               as SK
participant "binding.py"                  as BIND
participant "registry.py"                 as REG
participant "ComfyUI"                     as CUI
participant "OpenAPINode\n(typed subclass)" as N
participant "protocols/http.py"           as PRX
participant "codecs.py"                   as CDC
participant "API server\n(real or /api mock)" as API

== 1. Load-time — executed once when ComfyUI imports the package ==
U  -> LD  : spec_source\n(path / URL / preset:lm-studio / raw YAML)
LD -> SK  : pick handler by kind\n(openapi | asyncapi | graphql | mcp)
SK -> BIND : operation_to_input_types(op, components)
note right of BIND
  JSON Schema →
   - STRING / INT / FLOAT / BOOLEAN
   - enum → tuple-of-values (ComfyUI dropdown)
   - $ref  → resolved (depth ≤ 4, cycle-safe)
   - object → properties fanned out as slots
   - array / oneOf / allOf → multiline STRING JSON
end note
SK -> BIND : operation_to_return_types(op, components)
note right of BIND
  First 2xx JSON-schema properties →
  typed output slots (INT/FLOAT/STRING/BOOLEAN),
  followed by the canonical tail
  (body, stats, headers).
end note
BIND --> REG : (INPUT_TYPES, RETURN_TYPES, RETURN_NAMES)
REG  -> REG  : generate `OpenAPI_<preset>_<opId>` subclass\nCATEGORY = "API/<preset>"
REG  -> CUI  : NODE_CLASS_MAPPINGS, NODE_DISPLAY_NAME_MAPPINGS

== 2. Design-time — user edits the graph ==
U  -> CUI : drop node "API · lm-studio · chatCompletions"
CUI -> N : INPUT_TYPES()\n(typed widgets render)
N  --> CUI : STRING model, STRING messages, FLOAT temperature,\nINT max_tokens, BOOL stream, …
U  -> CUI : fill inputs, wire outputs

== 3. Run-time — graph executes a node ==
CUI -> N : invoke_typed(**slot_values)
N  -> N  : split params vs body props
N  -> PRX : execute(operation, method, server_url, values,\n           auth_scheme, credentials)
PRX -> CDC : encode request body\n(content-type negotiation)
CDC --> PRX : bytes
PRX -> API : HTTP request (or SSE / WS on other protocols)
API --> PRX : response bytes + Content-Type
PRX -> CDC : decode response\n(json / xml / form / msgpack / proto / bytes)
CDC --> PRX : dict / list / str
PRX --> N : Response(body, stats, headers, …)
N  -> N  : fan decoded fields into typed output slots
N  --> CUI : (slot_0, slot_1, …, body, stats, headers)
CUI --> U  : downstream nodes consume

== 4. Test-time — pytest ==
note over PRX, API
  In tests, `API` is the
  jbang WireMock facade
  in `/api/openapi/`, seeded
  from `/api/openapi/spec/lm-studio.yaml`.
  Same codepath — nothing in the
  node knows it's talking to a mock.
end note
@enduml
